<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6c78579d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s3073"><num value="3073">§ 3073.</num><heading> Medical and dental care</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may provide medical and dental care, including care in private facilities, for personnel of the Administration entitled to that care by law or regulation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6c78579e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/372/tII/s263">Pub. L. 107–372, title II, § 263</ref>, <date date="2002-12-19">Dec. 19, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/3093">116 Stat. 3093</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id6c78579f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id6c7857a0-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="id6c7857a1-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in <ref href="/us/usc/t33/s857–3/b">section 857–3(b) of this title</ref> prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/107/372">Pub. L. 107–372</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
